A 46-year-year-old man, Michael Nwoha, has been arrested for allegedly defiling three underage boys in Nkwelle Ezunaka in Oyi Local Government Area of Anambra State. The suspect reportedly assaulted the boys on different occasions. The Nation gathered that the suspect blamed the act on demons after he was arrested by police. Police spokesman Haruna Mohammed said the suspect would be arraigned after investigations. He said the suspect was arrested “following a tip-off,” saying he “allegedly had carnal knowledge against the order of nature with three small boys of between 6, 14 and 17 years on different occasions. “